Description: This is a great guitar. I love old Peavey's and buy just about every one I find for sale. They are simply one of the best playing values out there. It has a Maple 25.5 inch scale neck with a Rosewood fretboard a Basswood body with real binding. I put new d'addario extra light strings on it (my fav). I also gave it a good check out. Had a blast doing it too. You may want to have your tech adjust just the way you like it but I found it very easy to play as is. All the electronics work great. The action is nice and low. Intonation is right on. Truss rod is working and it's a double action one! The one bang on the upper back (pic 9) I made look as bad as possible. The light is really reflecting in the epoxy filler that was used. It hardly shows in normal light but it's there. Outside of normal player wear,pick scratches, back scratches all minimal for it's age that bang is the only real damage and it's on the back side. I will ship it in a serviceable old gig bag. The serial number and place of manufacturer were removed so I can't give exact information. I believe this model was made in Korea or China in the late 1990's or early 2000 period. It's great as is but easy to hotrod or put in a straight Tele 2 pickup combination. Please look closely and ask any questions you may have. We have more interesting items in other listings so please take a look. If we can combine shipping and save you money we are more then happy to. We know how special a guitar purchase is and we want you to have your item arrive safe and quickly. Your item will be completely insured as well. We are trying to build one of the best reputations possible on ebay. Thank you for taking a look. We will be growing our store into a full blown guitar store in 2019. Stay tuned!
